isocline
------------------------------------------
Isocline is a pure C library that can be used as an alternative to the GNU
readline library.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.5-1
  libisocline-devel-1.0.9-1bl1
  libisocline1-1.0.9-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.9.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.38-1
  cmake-3.23.2-1
  cygport-0.35.2-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  ninja-1.11.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/daanx/isocline

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/daanx/isocline/archive/refs/tags/v1.0.9.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack isocline-1.0.9-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./isocline-1.0.9-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/isocline-1.0.9-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/isocline-1.0.9-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libisocline1-1.0.9-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libisocline-devel-1.0.9-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(isocline)
  /usr/bin/isocline-example.exe
  /usr/bin/isocline-test_colors.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/isocline.README
  /usr/share/doc/isocline/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/isocline/README.md

(libisocline1)
  /usr/bin/cygisocline-1.dll

(libisocline-devel)
  /usr/include/isocline.h
  /usr/lib/libisocline.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/isocline.pc

------------------

Port Notes:

